data.text:
PASADENA – Nobel laureate and Egyptian global diplomat Ahmed Zewail will be the keynote speaker at Caltech’s 117th annual Commencement Ceremony on Friday.

Zewail, Caltech’s Linus Pauling professor of chemistry and professor of physics, is now taking a role in the development of Egypt’s political future and science infrastructure, Caltech officials said, and may be part of a post-Mubarak administration there.

Zewail, awarded the Nobel Prize in Chemistry in 1999, served on President Obama’s Council of Advisors on Science and Technology and was named U.S. Science Envoy to the Middle East in 2009.

In 2011, he was awarded the Priestley Medal, the highest honor of the American Chemical Society.

The commencement begins at 10 a.m. Friday at Caltech’s Beckman Auditorium, 332 S. Michigan Ave.
